  "text": "Here (·, ·) 2 is the quadratic Hilbert symbol. and ψ : F → C × is our fixed additive character. Note that the distinguished character χ 0 + equals the unitary distinguished character χ 0 ψ constructed in [CITATION_1] . One can show that in the 4k-fold covering case, the dependence on the choice of character ψ : F → C × disappears. We note that if we were to further assume µ 8 ⊂ F × , then (a, a) 2 = 1, and χ 0 + becomes essentially trivial. In any case, precisely one of these characters agrees with the choice of distinguished character implicit in [CITATION_2] .",
